    {
      "text": "The following table presents an analysis of fatty acid profiles derived from two distinct oil sources: Echium and Borage. These",
      "bbox": [
        15,
        462,
        580,
        474
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "oils have gained attention in the nutritional and pharmaceutical sectors due to their rich content of polyunsaturated fatty acids,",
      "bbox": [
        15,
        477,
        580,
        489
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "which are essential for various bodily functions. Notably, the table highlights the concentration of C16:0 (palmitic acid), a",
      "bbox": [
        15,
        493,
        580,
        505
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "prevalent saturated fatty acid that plays a crucial role in energy metabolism and cellular structure. The values indicate that",
      "bbox": [
        15,
        508,
        580,
        520
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Echium oil contains 7% C16:0, while Borage oil demonstrates a slightly lower concentration at 6.7%. This subtle difference in",
      "bbox": [
        15,
        524,
        580,
        536
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "fatty acid composition may influence the oils' nutritional applications and their effectiveness in promoting health outcomes.",
      "bbox": [
        15,
        539,
        580,
        551
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "Understanding these variations is vital for both consumers and manufacturers when considering the selection of oils for dietary",
      "bbox": [
        15,
        554,
        580,
        566
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "supplements and functional food formulations. Additionally, the implications of these findings extend to the broader context of",
      "bbox": [
        15,
        570,
        580,
        582
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "fatty acid research, where the balance between saturated and unsaturated fatty acids is essential for formulating health-oriented",
      "bbox": [
        15,
        585,
        580,
        597
      ]
    },
    {
      "text": "products. As the demand for plant-based alternatives continues to rise, these insights will inform future studies and product",
